  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Chartering Executive",
  "description": "<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Scope and Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Negotiate charter agreements with clients to secure optimal shipping terms.</li>\n  <li>Extensive global network of ship owners/tonnage providers and charterers.</li>\n  <li>Identify business opportunities related to cargoes &amp; tonnage</li>\n  <li>Analyze market trends and shipping rates to make informed decisions regarding chartering operations.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with operation teams to ensure timely loading and unloading of cargo.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate records of all charter agreements, communications, and transactions.</li>\n  <li>Optimize vessel allocation &amp; performance through regular assessments.</li>\n  <li>Monitor vessel performance and address any issues that may arise during transit.</li>\n  <li>Provide regular updates to management on chartering activities and market conditions.</li>\n  <li>Any other duties as may be assigned by the management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma / Degree in related studies </li>\n  <li>Able to work in a team environment independently with minimum supervision.</li>\n  <li>Experience in chartering is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in both English and Mandarin (required for communication with Mandarin-speaking associates).</li>\n  <li>Strong negotiation skills with a track record of successful contract management.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal, to effectively liaise with clients and partners.</li>\n  <li>Ability to analyze data and market trends to inform decision-making processes.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with maritime regulations and industry standards is a plus.</li>\n  <li>Must be available 24/7 via cellphone and committed to working beyond regular hours, including being on-call during critical voyage operations or emergencies.</li>\n</ul>",
